					<td valign="top" align='center'>
						<table height="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
							<tr>
							<td valign="top" align='center' width="95%">
								<table width="95%" height="100%" border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0">
									<tr><td valign="top" align="center"><br>
									<!-- strMainData goes here-->
									<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - DRUID</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>A FEW OPTIONS AVAILABLE</font> - <small>Aerillea, Tunare</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'>
<p>Tactics have to change once you reach level 50+ if you're a soloing druid.  For 49-52 there are a few quad kiting locations if you know where to go.&nbsp;<br>
<br>
For Quad Kiting you can do Spirocs in Timorous Deep from 49-52.  By 51 &amp; 52, you will have a hard time getting a lot of blues and you will have to settle for some greens in there.  But some exp is better then no exp.  Kiting Spirocs can be easy, but they can gate back to their starting location and yes they do train.  Harmony will work on them and they will be KOS to you if you switch to Wolf-form.  After killing them, your faction with them will drop and you'll be KOS to them in and out of Wolf-form.  You can also try Burning Woods as an alternative quad kiting Ash and Cinder Hornets.<br>
<br>
At 52-53, there is another good quad kiting spot in Timorous Deep.  I give credit to
Druid Master on the Druid Message board for this tidbit of information.  at around -9000, 3000 you will find yourself between two islands with some very mean raptors.  These raptors land a hit for about 100+ and they can take you down fast.  The small island usually has 4-6 raptors while the larger island has 8-12.  They train and they can be mean.  Most people prefer you kite on the small island while others prefer to kite them to the Chessboard at Loc -6500, 3000.  I only
recommend that you quad kite here if you have 200Wis with some good mana gear.  You are also unable to self-bind in
Timorous Deep if I forgot to mention that.  If you die here, it is unlikely you'll be able to get a rez without begging for one from another zone.  Raptors will be good exp till level 58.&nbsp;<br>
<br>
For the Soloing druid with low mana, the best place for you at 49+ is Burning Woods.  Plenty of blues all around and you can Root/dot here with ease.  I
recommended binding near the zone to The DreadLands as this is rarely ever populated by mobs.  Locate your target and proceed to root and dot it.  Root it using Grasping Roots (your very first root spell) and then dot it with Drifting Death and move away from the mob to get right in root distance and proceed to med.  When root breaks,
immediately reroot it again.  If you spaced yourself correctly, the mob will never touch you by the time you root it.  Reasons for using the lower level root is that its much more mana efficient.  Using higher levels of root is the dd damage way.  You want to conserve mana and this is the best way.  I've used all roots and I honestly prefer Grasping Roots for the low cast time, low mana, and its durability.  Beware of Sarnak Zealots as they have sow and will root you.  Best thing to do is root them back and gate back to your bind point (Keep gate memmed).  This will be good exp until level 53-54 and you should never have a hard time finding a blue to kill.  Prime targets would be Ash Hornets, Cinder Hornets, Tottering Gorillas, Forest Giant Arbors/Verdants/Ancients.  There are other
things you can take on here but they have quite a lot of HP.  Wurms, Mouldering Gorillas,
Scoriae Hornets and named Wurms.  Unless you feel like root/dotting for about 10 minutes, stick with the regulars. After this, and you prefer this method of gaining exp you can head to Skyfire at 54+  and do the same thing.  I haven't done this yet but I hear
that's the next best thing for a druid of that level.&nbsp;<br>
<br>
For the grouping Druid at 49+: Karnors and Sebilis are prime dungeons.  Elder Spiritist vambraces drop in Karnor's randomly and is a Druid Only armor piece.  This has a unlimited castable effect of Winged Death which can help you along with your dot/root ways.
<br>
<br>
</p>
</td></tr>
